.TH PV 1 "July 2026" "pv 0.5" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pv \- Pressure Valve: intelligent process lifecycle management
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pv
.RI [ COMMAND ]
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.nf
         .  .  .
        .  .  .  .
          _______
         /_______\e
        |\e \e   / /|
        | \e \e / / |
        |  \e V /  |
        |  /   \e  |
        | /     \e |
        |/_______\e|
          |  |  |
       ___|  |  |___
      /             \e
   __|               |__
  |___|             |___|
.fi
.PP
\fBpv\fR treats a process not as a PID that is either running or dead, but
as an \fIintent\fR with lifecycle semantics. It infers what each process is
trying to accomplish, predicts resource exhaustion before it happens, and
can suspend, resume, detach, and migrate work accordingly. The process is
no longer sacred; the objective is.
.PP
All state is read from \fI/proc\fR, \fI/sys\fR, and kernel PSI
(\fI/proc/pressure/*\fR). No daemon is required for the one-shot commands;
\fBpv daemon\fR adds continuous observation, habit learning, and
notifications.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B pv
Dashboard: pressure bars (CPU/RAM/IO/battery/thermals), the contextual
process view, and concrete recommendations.
.TP
.B pv ps
Contextual process list: each app with its inferred intent and lifecycle
capabilities (suspend, interrupt, migrate).
.TP
.B pv pressure
Detailed pressure breakdown, including memory burn rate and projected OOM
ETA when memory is genuinely draining.
.TP
.B pv explain
Plain-language explanation of the current system state.
.TP
.BI "pv intent " cmd...
Classify a command without running it: interruptibility, suspend safety,
migratability, GPU needs.
.TP
.BI "pv run -- " cmd...
Run a command as a detached session (setsid, logged). Survives terminal and
SSH disconnects.
.TP
.B pv sessions
List pv sessions with last log line.
.TP
.BI "pv attach " id
Follow a session's output; exits when the session ends.
.TP
.BI "pv suspend " target
Gracefully freeze an app (by name or pid): sync, SIGSTOP, record state.
Protected intents (ssh, runtimes, databases, package operations) are
refused unless \fB--force\fR.
.TP
.BI "pv resume " target
Thaw a suspended app.
.TP
.BI "pv kill " target
Terminate a suspended app (thaw, then SIGTERM).
.TP
.B pv suspended
List suspended apps with held memory and freeze age.
.TP
.BR "pv policy " [ --apply ] [ --init ]
Evaluate pressure policies from \fI~/.config/pv/policies.toml\fR. Dry-run by
default; \fB--apply\fR acts (suspend / renice+ionice / notify).
.TP
.BR "pv hosts " [ --init ]
List configured remote hosts with online probes.
.TP
.BI "pv migrate " target " [" --to " host" ]
Move restartable work (builds, encodes) to a remote host: rsync the working
directory, resume the command over ssh, stream output back. Refuses
non-migratable intents.
.TP
.BR "pv daemon " [ --interval " N" ] [ --desktop ] [ --install ]
Continuous observation: learns a per-hour demand profile, tracks variance,
and vents rustic valve-card notifications (8 valves: memory, demand spike,
reclaimable reserve, swap thrash, erratic demand, habit forecast, battery,
thermals). \fB--install\fR writes a systemd --user unit.
.TP
.BR "pv notify " [ --desktop ]
Emit valve cards for the current state, then exit.
.TP
.B pv habits
Show the learned per-hour demand profile.
.TP
.BR "pv live " [ --interval " N" ] [ --model " M" ] [ --no-infer ]
Persistent dynamic view: realtime metrics, RSS trend arrows, and a
streaming Groq inference panel. Inference re-fires on meaningful state
change or a 120 s heartbeat. Default model: llama-3.1-8b-instant.
.TP
.BR "pv update " [ --source ] [ --system ] [ --force ] [ --check ]
Self-update: latest GitHub release binary (fallback: clone + build from
source). Installs to \fI~/.local/bin\fR, or \fI/usr/local/bin\fR with
\fB--system\fR (via sudo). \fB--check\fR compares versions only.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/pv/policies.toml
Pressure policy rules (\fBpv policy --init\fR for defaults).
.TP
.I ~/.config/pv/hosts.toml
Remote hosts for migration (\fBpv hosts --init\fR for a template).
.TP
.I ~/.config/pv/groq_api_key
Groq API key (alternative to the environment variable).
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/pv/
State: sessions/, suspended.toml, habits.toml.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B GROQ_API_KEY
Groq API key for \fBpv live\fR inference. Without it the panel degrades to
an offline notice and metrics stay live.
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
Disable colored output.
.TP
.B PV_COLOR
Set to \fIalways\fR to force color when piping (e.g. to \fBless -R\fR).
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME / XDG_DATA_HOME
Override config/state locations (empty means unset, per spec).
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success; 1 on operational errors (unknown target, refused action,
failed migration); 2 on usage errors.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B pv suspend firefox
Freeze an idle browser, reclaiming its memory until resumed.
.TP
.B pv run -- cargo build --release
Detached, disconnect-proof build; follow with \fBpv attach\fR.
.TP
.B pv migrate cargo --to desktop
Rsync the workspace and resume the build on the remote host.
.TP
.B pv live --model llama-3.3-70b-versatile
Dynamic view with the sharper Groq model.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ps (1),
.BR top (1),
.BR kill (1),
.BR renice (1),
.BR systemctl (1),
.BR criu (8)
.PP
